---
title: "Graphs with at most one crossing"
collection: publications
permalink: /publication/leq_one_crossing
excerpt: ''
date: 2019-04-26
paperurl: 'https://arxiv.org/pdf/1901.09955.pdf'
citation: 'Silva, A.C., Arroyo, A., Richter, R.B. and Lee, O., 2019. Graphs with at most one crossing. arXiv preprint arXiv:1901.09955..'
---
The crossing number of a graph $$G$$ is the least number of crossings over all possible drawings of $$G$$. We present a structural characterization of graphs with crossing number one.
